od added to the THREE.Plane constructor\r\n\r\nAdded to the constructor? How so?\r\n\r\nWe already have `Plane.applyMatrix4( matrix )`, and several `Matrix4.makeRotation*()` methods for constructing a rotation matrix.","created_at":"2017-03-06T04:30:07.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/10923#issuecomment-284300401","id":284300401,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/10923","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI4NDMwMDQwMQ==","updated_at":"2017-03-06T04:30:07.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/284300401","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":2,"author_association":"NONE","body":"Object3D also has an applyMatrix() method, while also having rotation, rotateX, setRotationFromMatrix, and so on.  It seems these were added out of a concern for intuitive use, or case-specific use. It isn't an addition that is necessary, but it fits a similar use as rotateOnAxis vs. rotateX.","created_at":"2017-03-06T19:12:07.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/10923#issuecomment-284500008","id":284500008,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/10923","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI4NDUwMDAwOA==","updated_at":"2017-03-06T19:12:07.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/284500008","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/GitRyanPerrin\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/GitRyanPerrin\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/26066309?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/GitRyanPerrin","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/GitRyanPerrin\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/GitRyanPerrin","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/GitRyanPerrin\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI2MDY2MzA5","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/GitRyanPerrin\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/GitRyanPerrin\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/GitRyanPerrin\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"GitRyanPerrin","type":"User","id":26066309,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/GitRyanPerrin\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/GitRyanPerrin\/orgs"}},{"index":3,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"`Object3D` has a position and a local coordinate system. `Object3D.rotateX()` rotates the object around the x-axis in its local coordinate system.\r\n\r\nHow do you recommend applying this concept to `Plane`?\r\n\r\nWhich methods, specifically, do you recommend adding, and what would they do?","created_at":"2017-03-06T20:00:47.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/10923#issuecomment-284514341","id":284514341,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/10923","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI4NDUxNDM0MQ==","updated_at":"2017-03-06T20:00:47.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/284514341","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":4,"author_association":"NONE","body":"Here is an updated fiddle of me attempting to apply the concept. Unfortunately, it only worked the way it did in my previous fiddle.\r\n\r\nhttp:\/\/jsfiddle.net\/akmcv7Lh\/108\/\r\n\r\nI hope this will give you a better idea of what I think could be implemented. My issue in doing it myself was a lack of knowledge in JavaScript inheritance. I am a hobbyist, so this is a bit deeper into JavaScript than I have journeyed.\r\n\r\nIt seems to me that instead of doing plane.applyMatrix4( new THREE.Matrix4().makeRotationX( angle ) ), while easy, is much less intuitive. But applying this concept serves a similar purpose as object.rotateX( angle ) does for Object3D, where you could have used object.rotateOnAxis( new THREE.Vector3( 1, 0, 0 ) , angle );\r\n\r\nThe rotation of the plane would be in the world's coordinate system though, rather than the local.","created_at":"2017-03-07T22:54:27.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/10923#issuecomment-284887501","id":284887501,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/10923","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI4NDg4NzUwMQ==","updated_at":"2017-03-07T22:54:27.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/284887501","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/GitRyanPerrin\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/GitRyanPerrin\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/26066309?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/GitRyanPerrin","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/GitRyanPerrin\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/GitRyanPerrin","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/GitRyanPerrin\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI2MDY2MzA5","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/GitRyanPerrin\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/GitRyanPerrin\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/GitRyanPerrin\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"GitRyanPerrin","type":"User","id":26066309,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/GitRyanPerrin\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/GitRyanPerrin\/orgs"}},{"index":5,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":">The rotation of the plane would be in the world's coordinate system though, rather than the local.\r\n\r\nYes, and I do not find that very intuitive.\r\n\r\nI am trying to keep an open mind, but I do not see a compelling reason for adding methods to the library that rotate a plane around a world axis. I would consider such methods to be application-specific.\r\n\r\nAlso, we represent `THREE.Plane` in Hessian (Hesse) Normal Form, so the plane can be rotated by rotating the normal.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nTip: It is wise not to instantiate a new `Matrix4` (or `Vector3`) every frame unnecessarily. If you do not understand closures yet, at a minimum you can instantiate one `Matrix4` and reuse it. :)","created_at":"2017-03-07T23:56:25.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/10923#issuecomment-284900396","id":284900396,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/10923","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI4NDkwMDM5Ng==","updated_at":"2017-03-07T23:56:25.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/284900396","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":6,"author_association":"NONE","body":"That's fair, and thanks for the tip!","created_at":"2017-03-08T15:20:54.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/10923#issuecomment-285069910","id":285069910,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/10923","node